supportDesc.condition: Several leaves are damaged and the later addition (fols 56-62) which is a palimpsest is very fragile. Several lacunae.

layoutDesc.layout: Initials in various colours; rubrics in red ink.

decoDesc.decoNote: The initials opening each saga are littera florissae.

physDesc.additions: Fols 56-62 is a later addition. Several marginalia, especially personal names.

origin.p: Written in Iceland. The original part was written in the beginning of the fourteenth century while fols 56-62 can be dated to c. 1600.
Fol. 19 was previously a part of the collection of manuscripts, giventhe shelfmark AM 240 fol.. It is called liber vetuſtus, sed mutilus in AM 435 a 4to.

history.acquisition: Árni Magnússon acquired fols 17 and 18 from Jón Gíslason in 1706.

supportDesc.condition: The leaf was previously used as binding material.

history.origin: Written in Iceland c. 1250 ( Unger 1871 xxxix and Hreinn Benediktsson 1965 xlii ). Kålund's dating: The thirteenth century ( Katalog II 68 ).
history.acquisition: On an AM-slip, Árni Magnússon wrote: Þetta blad feck eg 1716. af Monſr Þorſteine Sigurdzſyne, hafdi hann þad feinged Nordur i landi, enn eigi i Auſtfiordum, og tok þad med ſier frä Islandi 1715 .
